WEBVTT

00:00:02.772 --> 00:00:04.275
<i>[singing voice] Aniplex.</i>

00:00:10.287 --> 00:00:13.393
[indistinct chatter]

00:00:15.965 --> 00:00:17.268
[exhales sharply]

00:00:20.440 --> 00:00:23.213
[beeping]

00:00:25.050 --> 00:00:28.691
[Mizuki] 940 milliseconds.
You've cleared it, Tatsuya!

00:00:29.425 --> 00:00:30.728
‐ Yes, finally.
‐ [chuckles nervously]

00:00:30.795 --> 00:00:32.799
Took until my third try
to clear it.

00:00:32.866 --> 00:00:34.536
I wouldn't have expected that.

00:00:34.603 --> 00:00:36.306
[Mizuki] So you really
do struggle

00:00:36.372 --> 00:00:37.842
with your practical skills,
don't you?

00:00:37.909 --> 00:00:39.880
[grunts]
Seriously?

00:00:40.280 --> 00:00:42.151
I haven't my incompetence
clear yet?

00:00:42.218 --> 00:00:44.990
Mm, well yes,
I did hear you say that.

00:00:45.057 --> 00:00:46.326
I thought it was modesty.

00:00:46.827 --> 00:00:47.762
[chuckles]

00:00:47.829 --> 00:00:49.198
Maybe I shouldn't say this.

00:00:49.265 --> 00:00:50.702
‐ [gasps]
‐ If I were average

00:00:50.768 --> 00:00:51.704
in practical skills,

00:00:51.770 --> 00:00:53.708
I probably wouldn't be
in this class.

00:00:54.075 --> 00:00:55.745
Yes, you're right.

00:00:56.179 --> 00:00:58.517
Although if you were good
at practical skills, too,

00:00:58.584 --> 00:01:01.657
you'd be way too perfect
and not very approachable,

00:01:01.724 --> 00:01:02.659
I think.

00:01:04.061 --> 00:01:05.163
Hey, Tatsuya?

00:01:05.230 --> 00:01:06.399
[Tatsuya] Hmm?

00:01:06.466 --> 00:01:08.270
[Mizuki] Do you feel bitter
about it?

00:01:08.905 --> 00:01:10.073
About what?

00:01:10.140 --> 00:01:12.344
Even though you really do
have talent,

00:01:12.411 --> 00:01:15.083
you've been evaluated as if
you don't have any at all.

00:01:15.450 --> 00:01:17.321
[Mizuki] Normally that'd
make someone bitter.

00:01:17.388 --> 00:01:18.991
You seem fine, though.

00:01:19.058 --> 00:01:20.828
It doesn't appear
to be bothering you much.

00:01:20.895 --> 00:01:24.235
Well, processing speed
is a crucial factor, too.

00:01:24.703 --> 00:01:26.172
[Tatsuya] You're not that
far off labeling me

00:01:26.239 --> 00:01:27.542
as unskilled.

00:01:27.609 --> 00:01:29.880
[Mizuki] And yet if you
actually implemented it,

00:01:29.947 --> 00:01:32.552
the truth of the matter is you
could activate it much faster,

00:01:32.619 --> 00:01:34.121
couldn't you?
‐ [grunts]

00:01:34.723 --> 00:01:35.992
[Tatsuya] Why do you
think that?

00:01:36.059 --> 00:01:37.729
During your first try,

00:01:37.796 --> 00:01:40.233
at one point you canceled
your magic sequence

00:01:40.300 --> 00:01:41.971
and rebuilt it from scratch.
Am I right?

00:01:42.404 --> 00:01:43.874
[Mizuki] And in terms
of the timing,

00:01:43.941 --> 00:01:45.578
you read the activation sequence

00:01:45.645 --> 00:01:48.551
and built your first
magic sequence simultaneously.

00:01:48.618 --> 00:01:51.189
Seeing that got me wondering
that for casting

00:01:51.255 --> 00:01:52.926
a low‐level spell like this,

00:01:52.993 --> 00:01:54.863
you could build
the magic sequence directly

00:01:54.930 --> 00:01:57.234
without using any activation
sequences at all.

00:01:58.436 --> 00:02:00.107
I never realized you
were capable

00:02:00.173 --> 00:02:01.510
of seeing that much.

00:02:02.077 --> 00:02:03.781
You really do have good eyes.

00:02:03.848 --> 00:02:05.017
[gasps]

00:02:05.417 --> 00:02:07.689
Sure,
for basic single systems spells,

00:02:07.756 --> 00:02:09.826
I guess I could invoke
more quickly

00:02:09.893 --> 00:02:11.664
if I built my sequence directly.

00:02:12.097 --> 00:02:14.302
However, not every single time.

00:02:14.368 --> 00:02:15.838
Not if it has too many steps.

00:02:16.573 --> 00:02:17.642
Think.

00:02:17.709 --> 00:02:19.378
<i>When you use magic</i>
<i>to move an egg</i>

00:02:19.445 --> 00:02:21.115
<i>from the kitchen to a table,</i>

00:02:21.182 --> 00:02:23.219
<i>it's a four‐process spell.</i>

00:02:24.523 --> 00:02:27.194
<i>Remove movement and suspension</i>
<i>from that spell,</i>

00:02:27.261 --> 00:02:30.902
<i>activation speeds up,</i>
<i>but the egg shell will break.</i>

00:02:32.772 --> 00:02:34.843
<i>However, to knock</i>
<i>your opponent backwards</i>

00:02:34.910 --> 00:02:36.179
<i>in battle,</i>

00:02:36.245 --> 00:02:38.083
<i>there's no need</i>
<i>to absorb the impact.</i>

00:02:38.149 --> 00:02:39.720
<i>It takes one process.</i>

00:02:40.855 --> 00:02:43.961
Since I hit my maximum
at five processes,

00:02:44.028 --> 00:02:45.163
it's all I can do.

00:02:45.230 --> 00:02:46.900
Well, I imagine
that five processes

00:02:46.967 --> 00:02:49.271
would be more than enough
for combat use.

00:02:49.338 --> 00:02:51.175
[chuckles]
But I'm not studying magic

00:02:51.242 --> 00:02:52.746
for combat use.

00:02:52.812 --> 00:02:56.052
My career goal is to use magic
in order to develop energy.

00:02:56.285 --> 00:02:57.454
To do that,

00:02:57.522 --> 00:02:59.425
I need multiple
process spells invoked

00:02:59.492 --> 00:03:01.229
by activation sequences.

00:03:01.730 --> 00:03:04.503
That's why I can deal
with being evaluated fairly.

00:03:04.569 --> 00:03:06.472
There's simply no way
of getting around it.

00:03:06.540 --> 00:03:08.677
It's due to my inferior
processing skills.

00:03:08.744 --> 00:03:09.846
Hmm?

00:03:09.913 --> 00:03:12.919
That's incredible, Tatsuya!
I'm so impressed!

00:03:12.986 --> 00:03:14.188
Huh?

00:03:14.255 --> 00:03:16.693
You can use magic
so you become a magician.

00:03:16.760 --> 00:03:19.231
At least that's the normal way
of doing things around here,

00:03:19.298 --> 00:03:20.635
but your reason
for studying magic

00:03:20.702 --> 00:03:22.839
is because you have
your own personal goals.

00:03:22.906 --> 00:03:25.912
Wait, now that I think about it,
that is true.

00:03:25.978 --> 00:03:29.251
‐ So, time for a fresh start.
‐ Uh, huh?

00:03:29.318 --> 00:03:32.257
At first I was only here
so I could study magic

00:03:32.324 --> 00:03:34.361
for the purpose
of controlling these eyes.

00:03:34.428 --> 00:03:35.998
It wasn't about wanting
to do anything.

00:03:36.065 --> 00:03:37.535
Not rally, at least.

00:03:37.602 --> 00:03:40.340
I think magic should be more
than just a means to an end.

00:03:40.842 --> 00:03:42.979
But from now on
I'll give it serious thought.

00:03:43.046 --> 00:03:44.448
Hey, hey, Mizuki.

00:03:44.516 --> 00:03:45.685
Yes, it's obvious,

00:03:45.752 --> 00:03:47.154
as long as we both
have conviction

00:03:47.221 --> 00:03:48.490
and a goal in mind.

00:03:48.557 --> 00:03:49.960
A little bit of slander
can't break our spirits,

00:03:50.026 --> 00:03:51.395
can it?

00:03:51.462 --> 00:03:53.266
And if the two of us can achieve
our cherished goals,

00:03:53.333 --> 00:03:56.072
our grades at this high school
are of secondary importance.

00:03:56.139 --> 00:03:58.243
That's what you
and I both live for, isn't it?

00:03:58.309 --> 00:04:01.115
Each individual should seek out
what they alone want to live for

00:04:01.182 --> 00:04:02.351
and then‐‐
‐ Jeez, Mizuki,

00:04:02.418 --> 00:04:04.589
what are you getting
all excited about?

00:04:08.062 --> 00:04:09.398
[whimpers]

00:04:09.465 --> 00:04:10.868
[Mizuka] Aww, sorry
to cause such a commotion.

00:04:10.935 --> 00:04:13.941
<i>[Tatsuya] My purpose,</i>
<i>it's nothing as grand as that.</i>

00:04:14.008 --> 00:04:15.845
<i>I had to be a magician</i>

00:04:15.912 --> 00:04:17.749
<i>even though</i>
<i>I'm not good at magic.</i>

00:04:21.790 --> 00:04:23.661
<i>It's like I've been cursed.</i>

