<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:06:00.487 --> 00:06:02.357
[Sayaka] You asked me a question
the other day.

00:06:03.026 --> 00:06:05.831
Originally, I suppose I thought
that letting the school know

00:06:05.898 --> 00:06:08.203
we weren't all about magic
would be enough.

00:06:09.171 --> 00:06:11.944
Now, though, I realize that
it's not nearly enough.

00:06:13.747 --> 00:06:15.651
What we want is simple.

00:06:15.718 --> 00:06:17.421
We're going to demand
that Magic High School

00:06:17.487 --> 00:06:18.924
improves our conditions.

00:06:21.395 --> 00:06:22.865
More specifically,
though,

00:06:22.932 --> 00:06:24.536
what is it that you want them
to improve?

00:06:24.603 --> 00:06:25.838
Well, everything!

00:06:25.905 --> 00:06:27.775
All aspects
of the way we're treated here.

00:06:27.842 --> 00:06:29.613
The main difference
that I have seen

00:06:29.679 --> 00:06:31.817
between course one
and course two students

00:06:31.883 --> 00:06:33.787
is the availability
or lack thereof

00:06:33.854 --> 00:06:35.758
of the curriculum's instructors.

00:06:35.825 --> 00:06:38.931
Would I be correct in assuming
that you want Magic High School

00:06:38.998 --> 00:06:40.735
to employ additional
faculty members?

00:06:40.801 --> 00:06:41.837
[gasps]

00:06:41.904 --> 00:06:44.308
I don't mean to take things
that far, but...

00:06:44.375 --> 00:06:46.613
So it's about club activities.

00:06:47.080 --> 00:06:50.086
It's my understanding that
the kendo and the kenjutsu teams

00:06:50.153 --> 00:06:52.725
are allotted the same amount
of practicing space.

00:06:53.727 --> 00:06:55.330
[groans]
That might be true,

00:06:55.397 --> 00:06:57.000
but that isn't really the point.

00:06:57.067 --> 00:06:59.438
Wait, are you saying
that you're not disgruntled?

00:06:59.506 --> 00:07:01.375
Disgruntled?
Of course.

00:07:01.442 --> 00:07:03.179
Uh, so then‐‐

00:07:03.246 --> 00:07:04.415
[Tatsuya] However...

00:07:04.983 --> 00:07:07.655
There's nothing in particular
that I think is necessary

00:07:07.722 --> 00:07:08.891
for the high school to alter.

00:07:08.958 --> 00:07:10.193
Huh?

00:07:10.260 --> 00:07:13.099
[Tatsuya] My expectations
with this educational facility

00:07:13.166 --> 00:07:14.435
only go so far.

00:07:15.170 --> 00:07:16.339
If I can gain access

00:07:16.405 --> 00:07:18.443
to unpublished
documents exclusive

00:07:18.510 --> 00:07:21.382
to Magic University
and receive my diploma

00:07:21.449 --> 00:07:22.986
from this affiliated
high school,

00:07:23.052 --> 00:07:24.522
then there
is nothing more than that

00:07:24.589 --> 00:07:26.092
which I shall be needing
from it.

00:07:27.127 --> 00:07:28.296
Besides...

00:07:28.731 --> 00:07:31.002
I'm not about to blame
the school's administration

00:07:31.068 --> 00:07:33.039
for students using slurs,

00:07:33.106 --> 00:07:35.043
which have been
expressly forbidden.

00:07:35.110 --> 00:07:36.513
[groans]

00:07:36.880 --> 00:07:39.418
Unfortunately, it would appear
that you and I don't share

00:07:39.485 --> 00:07:41.155
the same principles,
Miss Mibu.

00:07:47.434 --> 00:07:48.804
[gasps]

00:07:49.405 --> 00:07:50.841
[exhales]
[cell phone rings]

00:07:50.908 --> 00:07:51.877
Huh?

00:07:53.413 --> 00:07:54.649
[gasps]

00:07:58.456 --> 00:08:00.661
<i>[indistinct chatter]</i>

00:08:01.797 --> 00:08:03.567
[P.A. system squeals]
[all gasping]

00:08:03.634 --> 00:08:05.504
<i>[Boy] Attention, please,</i>
<i>all students.</i>

00:08:05.571 --> 00:08:08.811
<i>We are a volunteer coalition</i>
<i>opposed to discrimination.</i>

00:08:08.877 --> 00:08:10.981
Voluntary?
Right.

00:08:11.048 --> 00:08:14.421
<i>[Boy] We demand an opportunity</i>
<i>to negotiate on equal terms</i>

00:08:14.488 --> 00:08:17.562
with the student council
and extracurricular federation.

00:08:22.672 --> 00:08:24.108
[gasps]
Finally.

00:08:24.174 --> 00:08:25.310
[Tatsuya] Apologies.

00:08:25.377 --> 00:08:27.014
Okay, what's the situation?

00:08:27.080 --> 00:08:28.851
Our people have cut off
their power

00:08:28.917 --> 00:08:31.022
so they can't do
any more broadcasts.

00:08:31.088 --> 00:08:33.560
<i>[Mari] However, the coalition</i>
<i>has locked the door</i>

00:08:33.627 --> 00:08:35.363
<i>and barricaded</i>
<i>themselves inside.</i>

00:08:35.798 --> 00:08:37.502
<i>[Tatsuya] Can't we open it</i>
<i>from the outside?</i>

00:08:37.568 --> 00:08:39.004
<i>[Mari] We would,</i>
<i>but the problem is,</i>

00:08:39.071 --> 00:08:41.576
<i>they stole</i>
<i>the master key beforehand.</i>

00:08:41.943 --> 00:08:43.947
But that's clearly
criminal conduct.

00:08:44.014 --> 00:08:46.787
[Suzune] It is indeed,
and with that considered,

00:08:46.853 --> 00:08:48.824
this needs
to be handled delicately

00:08:48.891 --> 00:08:50.995
to discourage them
from blowing up any further.

00:08:51.062 --> 00:08:52.164
[grunts]

00:08:52.230 --> 00:08:54.836
That won't necessarily
deescalate anything.

00:08:54.903 --> 00:08:56.640
They won't suddenly
become docile

00:08:56.707 --> 00:08:58.443
just because we decide
to be discreet.

00:08:58.510 --> 00:09:00.013
Even if we use force,

00:09:00.080 --> 00:09:01.983
we should try to resolve
this quickly.

00:09:03.721 --> 00:09:05.290
And you,
Chairman Jumonji?

00:09:05.356 --> 00:09:06.793
[Tatsuya] What are your thoughts
on the matter?

00:09:07.562 --> 00:09:08.731
My thoughts?

00:09:08.797 --> 00:09:10.333
I don't think there's
any real downside

00:09:10.400 --> 00:09:12.304
to negotiating with them.

00:09:12.772 --> 00:09:14.743
[Katsuto] This was always just
a pretext.

00:09:14.809 --> 00:09:16.813
If we can refute that
strongly enough,

00:09:16.880 --> 00:09:19.485
it should assuage
their anxieties.

00:09:19.552 --> 00:09:21.088
If I'm understanding correctly,

00:09:21.155 --> 00:09:23.326
you're recommending
we just do nothing?

00:09:23.392 --> 00:09:24.696
As far as that goes,

00:09:24.763 --> 00:09:26.432
I haven't decided just yet.

00:09:26.733 --> 00:09:28.302
We can't allow their
unlawful behavior

00:09:28.369 --> 00:09:29.539
to go unpunished.

00:09:30.039 --> 00:09:31.810
[Katsuto] However,
I don't find it criminal enough

00:09:31.877 --> 00:09:33.814
to warrant destroying
school facilities

00:09:33.881 --> 00:09:35.885
for the sake
of a speedy resolution.

00:09:36.953 --> 00:09:37.889
[gasps]

00:09:38.690 --> 00:09:39.559
<i>[cell phone trilling]</i>

00:09:39.626 --> 00:09:40.895
[gasps]

00:09:42.765 --> 00:09:43.834
[Tatsuya] Is that you,
Miss Mibu?

00:09:43.901 --> 00:09:45.003
‐ This is Shiba.
‐ [gasps]

00:09:45.069 --> 00:09:47.274
I'm wondering,
where are you right now?

00:09:48.677 --> 00:09:50.881
Oh,
inside the broadcasting room.

00:09:50.948 --> 00:09:52.752
That's quite unfortunate
to hear.

00:09:52.819 --> 00:09:54.254
[both gasping]

00:09:54.321 --> 00:09:56.626
[Tatsuya] No, I wasn't
mocking you when you said that.

00:09:56.693 --> 00:09:57.862
‐ [grunts]
‐ [Tatsuya] I wish you would

00:09:57.929 --> 00:10:00.534
be calmer about this situation.
Yes.

00:10:01.035 --> 00:10:02.805
Excuse me.
If you don't mind,

00:10:02.872 --> 00:10:04.241
I'd like to cut to the chase.

00:10:04.308 --> 00:10:06.913
Chairman Jumonji has expressed
a willingness

00:10:06.980 --> 00:10:08.917
to negotiate with you.

00:10:08.984 --> 00:10:11.523
I've yet to confirm
the student council's position.

00:10:12.290 --> 00:10:15.396
No, wait.
The council will negotiate, too.

00:10:15.463 --> 00:10:19.171
Then we should discuss what time
and date we could schedule

00:10:19.238 --> 00:10:20.574
these negotiations.

00:10:21.342 --> 00:10:24.414
No, don't worry.
Your freedom is guaranteed.

00:10:24.782 --> 00:10:26.185
Yes.
Good.

00:10:26.252 --> 00:10:27.487
[phone beeps]

00:10:27.555 --> 00:10:28.924
She says they're coming out now.

00:10:28.991 --> 00:10:31.530
So was that Sayaka Mibu?

00:10:31.596 --> 00:10:32.732
[Tatsuya] Yes.

00:10:32.798 --> 00:10:34.234
She gave me
her cell phone number.

00:10:34.301 --> 00:10:36.807
Originally, it was just
so we could meet up later.

00:10:36.873 --> 00:10:38.710
Who knew it would come
in handy here?

00:10:38.777 --> 00:10:39.712
[Mari] You sure
don't waste time,

00:10:39.779 --> 00:10:40.614
do you?
‐ [Miyuki whimpers]

00:10:40.681 --> 00:10:41.716
Oh, come on.

00:10:41.883 --> 00:10:43.186
[Tatsuya] Anyway,

00:10:43.252 --> 00:10:45.290
I think we should get ourselves
into position.

00:10:45.356 --> 00:10:46.560
What do you mean?

00:10:47.027 --> 00:10:49.464
Prepare to take custody
of those people inside.

00:10:49.532 --> 00:10:51.368
You know,
if I remember correctly,

00:10:51.435 --> 00:10:52.738
didn't you just say
you would guarantee

00:10:52.805 --> 00:10:53.941
them all their freedom?

00:10:54.007 --> 00:10:56.078
The only one whose freedom
I guaranteed

00:10:56.145 --> 00:10:59.017
was Miss Sayaka Mibu,
and regardless,

00:10:59.084 --> 00:11:00.921
I never said I'm negotiating
on behalf

00:11:00.988 --> 00:11:02.457
of the disciplinary committee.

00:11:02.525 --> 00:11:03.927
[both gasping]

00:11:03.994 --> 00:11:06.265
[Miyuki] Brother,
you are undeniably evil.

00:11:06.332 --> 00:11:08.469
You're just now realizing that,
Miyuki?

00:11:08.537 --> 00:11:10.340
[Mikyuki giggles]
Fair enough.

00:11:10.406 --> 00:11:11.810
However, Brother...

00:11:12.444 --> 00:11:14.516
About the fact that you went
through all that trouble

00:11:14.582 --> 00:11:17.053
of saving Miss Mibu's
private cell phone number.

00:11:17.555 --> 00:11:19.626
I'll expect to hear all
the details about that

00:11:19.692 --> 00:11:21.195
from you later,
all right?

00:11:21.730 --> 00:11:22.965
[feet stomping]
[boys grunting]

00:11:23.032 --> 00:11:24.769
[Sayaka] What's the meaning
of this attack?

00:11:24.836 --> 00:11:27.073
You double crossed us!

00:11:27.140 --> 00:11:29.646
[Katsuto] Relax.
Shiba didn't double cross you.

00:11:29.712 --> 00:11:32.450
[gasps]
Chairman Jumonji.

00:11:32.885 --> 00:11:34.656
We will listen to your demands.

00:11:34.722 --> 00:11:37.060
However, complying
with your demands

00:11:37.127 --> 00:11:40.266
in this instance and approving
of the extreme measures you took

00:11:40.333 --> 00:11:41.335
are two different things.

00:11:41.402 --> 00:11:42.505
[grunts]

00:11:42.572 --> 00:11:44.576
[Mayumi] You're absolutely right
about that but...

00:11:44.842 --> 00:11:46.245
[Katsuto] Miss Saegusa?

00:11:46.312 --> 00:11:48.750
Disciplinary committee,
would you kindly release them?

00:11:49.418 --> 00:11:50.721
Hold on.

00:11:50.788 --> 00:11:52.257
[Mayumi] I know, Mari.
I know.

00:11:52.324 --> 00:11:55.330
However, we can't set up
the negotiations

00:11:55.396 --> 00:11:56.900
with Miss Mibu alone.

00:11:56.967 --> 00:11:58.904
As long as they're students
at this high school,

00:11:58.971 --> 00:12:00.708
we needn't view them
as flight risks.

00:12:00.774 --> 00:12:02.410
[gasps]
No, we would never run away!

00:12:03.580 --> 00:12:05.918
The school has decided
to leave this matter

00:12:05.985 --> 00:12:08.189
in the hands
of the student council.

00:12:08.256 --> 00:12:09.324
What?

00:12:09.391 --> 00:12:12.832
Mibu, let's go discuss
our pending negotiations

00:12:12.898 --> 00:12:14.769
with your volunteer coalition.

00:12:15.169 --> 00:12:16.506
[Mayumi] Would you mind coming
with me?

00:12:16.573 --> 00:12:18.142
Sure, just lead the way.

00:12:24.822 --> 00:12:27.160
[whispering]

00:12:34.809 --> 00:12:36.980
[indistinct chatter]

00:12:38.082 --> 00:12:39.451
‐ [Tatsuya] Excuse me.
‐ Hmm?

00:12:39.519 --> 00:12:40.955
Could we speak with you, please?

00:12:41.021 --> 00:12:43.426
[Mayumi] Oh, Tatsuya.
And Miyuki.

00:12:43.492 --> 00:12:44.494
What's the matter?

00:12:44.562 --> 00:12:46.298
About yesterday's incident.

00:12:50.440 --> 00:12:52.277
[Mayumi] They want
equal treatment between

00:12:52.344 --> 00:12:54.481
the course one
and the course two students.

00:12:55.283 --> 00:12:57.888
However, they don't seem
to have figured out exactly

00:12:57.955 --> 00:12:59.525
how they want
to change things.

00:12:59.592 --> 00:13:02.130
If anything, I sense they wanted
the student council

00:13:02.197 --> 00:13:03.533
to come up with the next steps.

00:13:03.600 --> 00:13:06.806
Then it devolved into
an emotional back and forth.

00:13:07.240 --> 00:13:10.614
We decided to hold a forum
which will take place tomorrow

00:13:10.681 --> 00:13:11.816
when school gets out.

00:13:11.883 --> 00:13:14.454
That compromise happened
pretty quickly.

00:13:15.223 --> 00:13:17.460
And while I do understand
the strategy

00:13:17.528 --> 00:13:20.466
of not giving your opponent time
to prepare,

00:13:20.534 --> 00:13:21.503
by the same token,

00:13:21.569 --> 00:13:23.807
we'll have just
as little time ourselves.

00:13:23.874 --> 00:13:25.778
Which members
of the student council

00:13:25.844 --> 00:13:27.414
are participating in this forum?

00:13:28.650 --> 00:13:29.986
[giggles]

00:13:30.353 --> 00:13:31.488
[both gasping]

00:13:31.556 --> 00:13:33.459
Don't tell me you're going
to be the only one.

00:13:33.527 --> 00:13:34.796
[gasps]

00:13:35.196 --> 00:13:36.733
Since we're all running low
on time,

00:13:36.800 --> 00:13:38.402
if I'm the one up there,

00:13:38.469 --> 00:13:41.710
they won't rip me to shreds over
minor differences of opinion.

00:13:42.344 --> 00:13:44.181
I'm more afraid
of impression manipulation

00:13:44.247 --> 00:13:46.251
making this too emotional.

00:13:46.318 --> 00:13:48.022
So that they couldn't get
the best of you

00:13:48.089 --> 00:13:49.491
in a logical dispute.

00:13:49.559 --> 00:13:50.928
[grunts]

00:13:51.495 --> 00:13:52.531
And besides...

00:13:57.107 --> 00:13:58.710
[Mayumi] If for some reason
those students

00:13:58.777 --> 00:14:00.714
have solid enough reasons
to defeat me

00:14:00.781 --> 00:14:02.217
in a fair,
level‐headed debate...

00:14:02.283 --> 00:14:03.419
[gasps]

00:14:04.889 --> 00:14:07.293
Then all the student council
would have to do

00:14:07.360 --> 00:14:09.899
is integrate that into how
we run this school.

00:14:10.801 --> 00:14:13.005
[indistinct chatter]

00:14:13.072 --> 00:14:15.309
[Boy] Course two students,
listen up!

00:14:15.376 --> 00:14:17.648
Our coalition seeks
to eradicate discrimination

00:14:17.715 --> 00:14:19.217
at this school!

00:14:19.284 --> 00:14:21.488
[Girl] As the student council
president announce this morning,

00:14:21.556 --> 00:14:23.627
tomorrow there will be
an open forum regarding

00:14:23.693 --> 00:14:26.566
the treatment of course one
and two students.

00:14:26.633 --> 00:14:28.770
[Boy] This is our best chance
to improve conditions

00:14:28.837 --> 00:14:30.473
for all us course two students!

00:14:30.541 --> 00:14:32.377
Please attend tomorrow's
open forum.

00:14:32.444 --> 00:14:33.680
It's important.

00:14:33.747 --> 00:14:35.249
‐ [Mizuki] Um, well‐‐
‐ Hmm?

00:14:35.316 --> 00:14:37.922
[Mikuzi] Maybe I actually don't.

00:14:38.289 --> 00:14:40.493
It's just,
that isn't what I want.

00:14:40.561 --> 00:14:41.495
[Tatsuya] Mizuki!

00:14:41.563 --> 00:14:43.332
Oh, hey, Tatsuya.

00:14:45.871 --> 00:14:47.273
<i>[Tatsuya] I know this guy.</i>

00:14:49.311 --> 00:14:50.981
[grunts]

00:14:51.649 --> 00:14:53.319
I'm Officer Shiba.

00:14:53.887 --> 00:14:55.490
According
to the disciplinary committee,

00:14:55.557 --> 00:14:57.828
holding someone against
their will is unlawful,

00:14:57.895 --> 00:14:59.297
so please refrain.

00:14:59.364 --> 00:15:01.301
‐ Miss Shibata.
‐ [gasps]

00:15:01.368 --> 00:15:03.205
[Kinoe] I can make any time work
for me,

00:15:03.272 --> 00:15:05.243
so if you change your mind,
just let me know.

00:15:05.309 --> 00:15:06.378
Goodbye.

00:15:06.813 --> 00:15:07.982
Oh.

00:15:08.950 --> 00:15:10.521
Do you know that guy?

00:15:10.587 --> 00:15:12.691
[Mizuki] Yes, he's the captain
of the kendo team.

00:15:12.758 --> 00:15:15.463
We just met,
but his name is Kinoe Tsukasa.

00:15:15.531 --> 00:15:17.066
He sees spirit
particle emissions

00:15:17.133 --> 00:15:18.670
the same as I do.

00:15:18.737 --> 00:15:21.041
<i>[Tatsuya] I knew those glasses</i>
<i>weren't only for style.</i>

00:15:21.108 --> 00:15:22.377
He was asking if I wanted

00:15:22.444 --> 00:15:24.414
to join
an extracurricular organization

00:15:24.481 --> 00:15:27.220
of other students afflicted
with the same hypersensitivity.

00:15:27.287 --> 00:15:28.790
So that's what he wanted?

00:15:28.857 --> 00:15:31.028
I kept turning him down
telling him I had my hands full

00:15:31.094 --> 00:15:32.565
with my classes.

00:15:33.132 --> 00:15:35.002
<i>[Tatsuya] Captain</i>
<i>of the kendo team.</i>

00:15:35.069 --> 00:15:36.973
<i>Kinoe Tsukasa, huh?</i>

00:15:39.712 --> 00:15:43.052
[Yakumo] Kinoe Tsukasa,
formerly known as Kinoe Kamono.

00:15:43.119 --> 00:15:45.189
None of his parents
nor grandparents seem

00:15:45.256 --> 00:15:47.327
to possess any propensity
for magic.

00:15:47.862 --> 00:15:50.032
They're a so‐called
ordinary family.

00:15:50.099 --> 00:15:52.470
It's actually part
of the onmyoji,

00:15:52.538 --> 00:15:54.942
an often‐overlooked branch
of the Kamo clan.

00:15:55.009 --> 00:15:58.783
Kinoe's eyes must be some sort
of throwback to his ancestors.

00:15:59.619 --> 00:16:01.589
Master, did you already know
that I wanted you

00:16:01.656 --> 00:16:03.593
to look
into Kinoe Tsukasa's past?

00:16:03.660 --> 00:16:04.662
No.

00:16:04.729 --> 00:16:06.231
It had nothing to do
with your request.

00:16:06.298 --> 00:16:08.068
I simply knew about him already.

00:16:08.537 --> 00:16:11.208
It may be true that I'm a priest
but even more than that,

00:16:11.275 --> 00:16:13.445
I consider myself a shinobi.

00:16:14.047 --> 00:16:16.118
Any individual with a background
that might prove

00:16:16.185 --> 00:16:18.489
to be problematic
for society someday,

00:16:18.557 --> 00:16:21.395
I make a point
of investigating each one.

00:16:22.096 --> 00:16:23.967
[Tatsuya] Have you
investigated us, too?

00:16:25.069 --> 00:16:27.040
It's certainly not
for lack of trying,

00:16:27.106 --> 00:16:29.444
but when I first started,
I didn't know.

00:16:29.846 --> 00:16:31.950
[Yakumo] The intelligence
manipulation concerning you two

00:16:32.016 --> 00:16:33.352
is ironclad.

00:16:33.419 --> 00:16:36.391
I really must tip my hat
to the both of you for that.

00:16:37.293 --> 00:16:39.030
Excuse me, Master.

00:16:39.364 --> 00:16:41.870
But does Mr. Tsukasa
have any connection to Blanche?

00:16:42.403 --> 00:16:44.307
‐ [grunts]
‐ [gasps]

00:16:45.076 --> 00:16:47.313
<i>[Yakumo] Kinoe's mother's</i>
<i>second husband's child</i>

00:16:47.380 --> 00:16:48.783
<i>with his first wife,</i>

00:16:48.850 --> 00:16:51.355
<i>meaning Kinoe's Tsukasa's</i>
<i>older stepbrother</i>

00:16:51.421 --> 00:16:54.595
<i>is the secret mastermind</i>
<i>of Blanche's Japanese branch,</i>

00:16:54.662 --> 00:16:57.200
and the shadowy figure named
Hajime Tsukasa,

00:16:57.267 --> 00:16:59.471
he's more than
a symbolic figurehead.

00:16:59.539 --> 00:17:01.509
He's the genuine leader
who also runs

00:17:01.576 --> 00:17:05.149
their covert operations,
including illegal activities.

00:17:05.851 --> 00:17:08.723
Kinoe Tsukasa's enrollment
at Magic High School

00:17:08.790 --> 00:17:11.963
must be due to the influence
of Hajime Tsukasa.

00:17:12.598 --> 00:17:15.469
<i>As for the school's</i>
<i>open forum tomorrow...</i>

00:17:22.183 --> 00:17:24.689
Hajime might
be plotting something nefarious.

00:17:42.290 --> 00:17:44.294
<i>[Boy] Compared</i>
<i>to course one students,</i>

00:17:44.361 --> 00:17:47.133
treatment of course two students
<i>is inferior in all ways!</i>

00:17:47.433 --> 00:17:48.770
Confess, chairwoman.

00:17:48.837 --> 00:17:51.341
Aren't you trying to hide
the obvious truth of that?

00:17:51.408 --> 00:17:53.445
[Mayumi] You just said
that this inferior treatment

00:17:53.513 --> 00:17:54.715
was in all ways.

00:17:54.782 --> 00:17:56.719
Could you please
give specific examples

00:17:56.786 --> 00:17:58.055
of what you're referring to?

00:17:58.523 --> 00:18:00.694
[Boy] Magic‐oriented clubs
with high ratios

00:18:00.761 --> 00:18:03.265
of course one students received
the lion's share

00:18:03.332 --> 00:18:06.004
of the budget compared
to the non‐magical clubs,

00:18:06.071 --> 00:18:08.977
which are mainly populated
by the course two students.

00:18:09.444 --> 00:18:11.381
Isn't that proof
that preferential treatment

00:18:11.448 --> 00:18:13.753
for course one students
is overlooked even

00:18:13.820 --> 00:18:15.323
in extracurricular clubs?

00:18:20.032 --> 00:18:23.773
Even non‐magical activities such
as the school football team...

00:18:24.407 --> 00:18:26.278
Which has compiled
an excellent record

00:18:26.345 --> 00:18:28.984
have been allotted budgetary
funding each semester...

00:18:29.050 --> 00:18:31.188
This is no longer
an open debate.

00:18:31.254 --> 00:18:33.760
It's nothing more than a speech
by Mayumi.

00:18:34.729 --> 00:18:36.198
But even so,

00:18:36.264 --> 00:18:38.570
I have no clue what
their true intentions are,

00:18:38.637 --> 00:18:41.408
but we can't make
any advances ourselves.

00:18:41.475 --> 00:18:44.114
A defense‐only policy
sounds nice, but‐‐

00:18:44.180 --> 00:18:45.684
‐ Please, chairwoman.
‐ [gasps]

00:18:45.751 --> 00:18:48.222
Don't make assumptions
about resorting to violence.

00:18:48.288 --> 00:18:49.391
[Mari] I know.

00:18:49.457 --> 00:18:50.861
You don't have
to worry about that.

00:18:50.927 --> 00:18:52.063
[Suzune] I'm counting on you

00:18:52.130 --> 00:18:53.733
[Mayumi] Of possible
discrimination

00:18:53.800 --> 00:18:55.804
in the circumstances
you pointed out

00:18:55.871 --> 00:18:56.773
because after all...

00:18:57.941 --> 00:18:59.144
Blooms and Weeds.

00:18:59.210 --> 00:19:00.547
[all gasping]

00:19:00.614 --> 00:19:01.883
[Mayumi] These terms are banned
by the school,

00:19:01.949 --> 00:19:04.287
the student council,
and the disciplinary committee.

00:19:04.354 --> 00:19:06.258
Unfortunately, though,
I must admit,

00:19:06.325 --> 00:19:07.761
they are still in wide use.

00:19:07.828 --> 00:19:08.997
[Boy] Hey, wait.
What does that mean?

00:19:09.064 --> 00:19:10.600
[Boy 2] Is that cool to say now?

00:19:10.667 --> 00:19:13.573
In fact some core two students
deprecate themselves as Weeds

00:19:13.640 --> 00:19:15.677
and are even resigned
to accept it.

00:19:15.744 --> 00:19:18.048
‐ What'd she say?
‐ There's no such thing!

00:19:18.115 --> 00:19:19.417
[Mayumi] Exist here.

00:19:19.484 --> 00:19:22.056
The issue is this barrier
to awareness.

00:19:22.423 --> 00:19:24.795
As Magic High School's
student council president,

00:19:24.862 --> 00:19:28.135
it is this very barrier that I
have been determined

00:19:28.202 --> 00:19:29.605
to break down for all of us.

00:19:31.174 --> 00:19:33.513
But creating new
discriminatory practices

00:19:33.580 --> 00:19:36.719
is not the way this situation
should be resolved.

00:19:37.220 --> 00:19:41.596
We all from course one to two
are students of this school,

00:19:41.662 --> 00:19:44.869
and the time we spend here
as students will someday

00:19:44.935 --> 00:19:47.741
become memories
that are indeed irreplaceable.

00:19:47.808 --> 00:19:50.747
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:19:50.814 --> 00:19:54.354
[applause]

00:19:54.421 --> 00:19:58.195
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:19:58.262 --> 00:19:59.431
[gasps]

00:19:59.497 --> 00:20:01.769
Now, I would like
to take this opportunity

00:20:01.836 --> 00:20:03.807
to tell the entire student body
what my hopes

00:20:03.873 --> 00:20:05.009
for the future are.

00:20:05.076 --> 00:20:07.447
There is still a system
in the student council

00:20:07.514 --> 00:20:09.217
that discriminates
against course one

00:20:09.284 --> 00:20:10.754
and two students.

00:20:11.923 --> 00:20:13.492
Under the current system,

00:20:13.560 --> 00:20:15.697
all officers except
for the president

00:20:15.764 --> 00:20:16.733
must be nominated

00:20:16.799 --> 00:20:18.402
from among
the course one students.

00:20:18.469 --> 00:20:20.741
This regulation
can only be overhauled during

00:20:20.807 --> 00:20:22.243
the general assembly
which convenes during

00:20:22.310 --> 00:20:23.412
the reelection

00:20:23.479 --> 00:20:24.949
of the student
council president.

00:20:25.015 --> 00:20:27.654
Therefore, my final official act

00:20:27.721 --> 00:20:29.491
as the school's student
council president

00:20:29.558 --> 00:20:31.194
will be to eliminate
this regulation

00:20:31.261 --> 00:20:32.698
at the general assembly.

00:20:33.165 --> 00:20:36.539
People's hearts and minds cannot
be changed through brute force,

00:20:36.606 --> 00:20:40.279
and because of that,
for the remainder of my term,

00:20:40.346 --> 00:20:41.516
I will strive

00:20:41.582 --> 00:20:43.953
to see this vision come
to fruition.

00:20:44.020 --> 00:20:45.322
[grunts]

00:20:45.389 --> 00:20:48.495
[cheers and applause]

00:20:58.850 --> 00:20:59.752
[booming]
[grunts]

00:21:03.358 --> 00:21:06.298
<i>[tense music]</i>

00:21:06.364 --> 00:21:07.300
<i>♪♪ ♪♪</i>

00:21:07.366 --> 00:21:09.237
[all screaming]

00:21:12.243 --> 00:21:14.414
‐ Chairwoman!
‐ Apprehend them now!

00:21:14.515 --> 00:21:15.717
[both grunting]

00:21:15.784 --> 00:21:16.686
[groans]

00:21:16.752 --> 00:21:18.890
[grunts]
[glass shattering]

00:21:19.290 --> 00:21:20.827
[all screaming]

00:21:24.000 --> 00:21:25.937
[all screaming]

00:21:26.004 --> 00:21:27.440
<i>[Tatsuya] Gas bomb?</i>

00:21:27.508 --> 00:21:28.977
[Gyobu] Hold your breath!
Don't inhale the smoke!

00:21:32.216 --> 00:21:34.320
Got it.
[grunts]

00:21:36.993 --> 00:21:39.965
<i>[Tatsuya] Convergence of the</i>
<i>gas in a movement spell.</i>

00:21:40.032 --> 00:21:41.903
<i>Guy spiked the gas bomb,</i>
<i>smoke and all,</i>

00:21:41.969 --> 00:21:44.073
<i>in that one instant.</i>
<i>Very impressive.</i>

00:21:44.140 --> 00:21:45.811
[both grunting]

00:21:46.244 --> 00:21:47.614
[chuckles]
[distant booming]

00:21:47.981 --> 00:21:48.917
[all shouting]

00:21:48.983 --> 00:21:50.286
[guns cocking]

00:21:50.352 --> 00:21:53.192
[electric sparking]
[both groaning]

00:21:53.258 --> 00:21:55.362
[all gasping]

00:21:56.231 --> 00:21:57.868
<i>[Tatsuya] An MID field.</i>

00:21:57.935 --> 00:22:00.841
Did she just flood the gas masks
<i>with nitrogen?</i>

00:22:01.742 --> 00:22:02.578
[gasps]

00:22:02.644 --> 00:22:04.414
More intruders?
Over there, too?

00:22:04.480 --> 00:22:05.684
[grunts]
[gunshot]

00:22:06.051 --> 00:22:07.721
[all shouting]

00:22:10.861 --> 00:22:12.396
[shouts]

00:22:14.467 --> 00:22:15.504
[exhales]

00:22:15.570 --> 00:22:16.404
‐ Chairwoman!
‐ [grunts]

00:22:16.471 --> 00:22:17.875
I'd better go.

00:22:17.941 --> 00:22:19.879
There was a detonation
at the practical skills wing.

00:22:19.945 --> 00:22:22.016
‐ Tatsuya.
‐ [Miyuki] Brother!

00:22:22.083 --> 00:22:23.418
I'm going with you.

00:22:24.020 --> 00:22:25.322
[grunts]

